header.gameNote: SHELBY METCALF CLASSIC AT COLLEGE STATION TX

article.headline: Lamar 71, Louisiana Tech 68
article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- James Davis scored 35 points and Lamar Sanders had a triple-double to lead Lamar to a 71-68 victory over Louisiana Tech on Sunday in the Shelby Metcalf Classic at Texas A&M. Davis shot 13-of-18 from the field and made 9 of 10 free throws. Sanders had 11 points, 12 assists and 13 rebounds for Lamar (2-2). Davis hit a pair of free throws with 2:16 left to pull Lamar within one of Louisiana Tech (0-3). A jumper by Terry Parker extended Louisiana Tech's lead to 68-65, but Sanders responded with a layup and Matthew Barrow and Darren Hopkins each made two free throws in the final minute to give Lamar the victory. Parker and Marcus Elliott each had 13 points to lead the Bulldogs. Trey McDowell and Chad McKenzie each added 11 and Harry Disy had 10. Lamar shot 50 percent from the field and Louisiana Tech shot 41 percent. The Cardinals led 34-33 at the half.
